   ----------------------------
   Installation 
   ----------------------------

Installation Guide

  Please read the topics in this guide from top to bottom.
  
  [Hint:] C5Connector.Java uses the state-of-the-art logging facade {{{http://http://www.slf4j.org}SLF4J}}.
          Read the corresponding manual, if you are not familiar with it.
          
* Prepare the Installation

  There isn't any download provided at the moment. But the desired jar file can be easily build with maven2. 
  Just download the source, declare a preferred SLF4J binding in the dependencies section of your POM within 
  the runtime scope and call the following command:
  
+------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
mvn clean package
+------------------------------------------------------------------------------+

  It creates a zip file like <<<c5connector-java-[version]-SNAPSHOT-bin.zip>>> which contains all binaries
  of the project dependencies. Simply put these files in your classpath (usually <<<WEB-INF/lib>>>).

* Activation of the Connector Servlet

  [Hint:] The declaration of the servlet is mandatory, it is disabled by default for security reasons!
  
  []
   
  It takes three steps to enabled it.
  
  [[1]]  Declare the ConnectorServlet in your <<<web.xml>>>:

+------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
  <servlet>
  	<servlet-name>ConnectorServlet</servlet-name>
  	<servlet-class>de.thischwa.c5c.ConnectorServlet</servlet-class>
  	<load-on-startup>1</load-on-startup>
  </servlet>
  
  <servlet-mapping>
  	<servlet-name>ConnectorServlet</servlet-name>
  	<url-pattern>/filemanager/connectors/java/*</url-pattern> 	
  </servlet-mapping>
+------------------------------------------------------------------------------+

  Assuming you installed the editor in the <<</filemanager>>> folder in your webapp.\
  The Connector Servlet is now declared but <still> disabled. 

  [[2]] Create a <<<c5connector.properties>>> file in your classpath and add:
  
+------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
connector.userActionImpl = de.thischwa.c5c.requestcycle.impl.EnabledUserAction
+------------------------------------------------------------------------------+

  [[3]] The following variables need to be changed in <<<filemanager.config.js>>>:
  
+------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
var lang = 'java';
+------------------------------------------------------------------------------+

  Be sure, that <<<imagesExt>>> is equivalent to the C5Connector properties for the allowed
  image extensions!